TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$x1 = random(13,23,1);
$y1 = random(21,43,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The equation of the line that goes through the point
\( ( $x1 ,$y1 ) \) and is parallel to the \(x\)-axis can be written in the form
\( y = mx+b \) where \( m \) 
is: \{ans_rule(15) \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = 0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
and  where \( b \) is: \{ans_rule(15) \}
$BR
EOT
$ans = $y1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

